In a speech at the National Constitution Center in Philadelphia, President Biden addressed the importance of protecting the right to vote. He emphasized that the right to vote freely and have one's vote counted is fundamental to democracy. He highlighted the historic turnout and scrutiny of the 2020 election and called out efforts to undermine the integrity of elections through voter suppression and election subversion. Biden urged the passage of the For the People Act and the John Lewis Voting Rights Advancement Act to combat these threats. He also emphasized the need for a coalition of Americans to defend democracy and ensure that the power remains with the people. Biden warned that the assault on free and fair elections is a significant test of democracy and called on Americans to act to protect and strengthen democracy.